# Your MERN Stack Application

Generated by `create-mern-app`

## Project Structure

- `package.json`: Root configuration for the monorepo.
- `client/`: React frontend (Vite).
- `server/`: Express backend (Node.js).

## Key Scripts (at the root)

- `npm run dev`: Starts both frontend and backend concurrently.
- `npm run client`: Starts only the React frontend.
- `npm run server`: Starts only the Express backend.
- `npm run install-all`: Installs all dependencies for root, client, and server.

## Folder Conventions

### Backend (`/server`)
- `routes/`: Define your API endpoints.
- `controllers/`: Logic for your routes.
- `models/`: Mongoose database schemas.
- `middleware/`: Custom Express middleware.

### Frontend (`/client`)
- `src/components/`: Reusable UI components.
- `src/pages/`: Main application views/pages.
- `src/hooks/`: Custom React hooks.
- `src/services/`: API call logic (Axios, etc.).

